docs.name: NASDAQ OMX Geothermal (GRNGEO)
docs.description:
The NASDAQ OMX Geothermal Index is a sub sector index of the Green Economy Index designed to track companies that produce energy through geothermal power. The Geothermal Index rolls up to the primary sector Renewable Energy Generation Index. The Index began dissemination on October 13, 2010 with an initial value of 1000.00.

Components: 7

Currency: USD

Entitlements: NASDAQ OMX Green Economy Family

Total Market Value: is the sum of the market value of all companies in the index.

Dividend Market Value: is the sum of the market value of all dividends generated by companies in the index.

Terms of Use: This data cannot be republished or used as the basis of a financial product without the permission of Nasdaq OMX.

docs.name: NASDAQ ASPA Index (NQASPA)
docs.description:
The NASDAQ ASPA Index is a float adjusted market capitalization-weighted index which includes securities in countries located in Asia Pacific.The Index began on December 3, 2012 at a base value of 1000.00.

Components: 3,807

Currency: USD

Entitlements: NASDAQ Global Index Family

Total Market Value: is the sum of the market value of all companies in the index.

Dividend Market Value: is the sum of the market value of all dividends generated by companies in the index.

Terms of Use: This data cannot be republished or used as the basis of a financial product without the permission of Nasdaq OMX.

docs.name: NASDAQ-100 (NDX)
docs.description:
The NASDAQ-100 Index includes 100 of the largest domestic and international non-financial securities listed on The NASDAQ Stock Market based on market capitalization. The Index reflects companies across major industry groups including computer hardware and software, telecommunications, retail/wholesale trade and biotechnology. It does not contain securities of financial companies including investment companies.

Components: 107

Currency: USD

Entitlements: U.S. Classic (NASDAQ / PHLX)

Total Market Value: is the sum of the market value of all companies in the index.

Dividend Market Value: is the sum of the market value of all dividends generated by companies in the index.

Terms of Use: This data cannot be republished or used as the basis of a financial product without the permission of Nasdaq OMX.

docs.name: Apple Inc. (AAPL)
docs.description:
End of day open, high, low, close and volume, dividends and splits, and split/dividend adjusted open, high, low close and volume for Apple Inc. (AAPL). Ex-Dividend is non-zero on ex-dividend dates. Split Ratio is 1 on non-split dates. Adjusted prices are calculated per CRSP (www.crsp.com/products/documentation/crsp-calculations)
